- Hello.
- Yes?

7
00:00:31,949 --> 00:00:34,576
- Oh, my.
- I came to sell this book.

8
00:00:34,660 --> 00:00:35,869
Oh, you're...

9
00:00:37,037 --> 00:00:38,914
<i>- Dweji-gomtang! </i>Right?
- Yes, that's me.

10
00:00:38,997 --> 00:00:40,040
OK DONG-SIK
CHEF, BUSINESSMAN

11
00:00:40,541 --> 00:00:42,292
- Come this way.
- Okay.

12
00:00:42,751 --> 00:00:44,294
It's an honor.

13
00:00:44,378 --> 00:00:46,255
- You made the reservation?
- Yes.

14
00:00:46,338 --> 00:00:47,798
<i>- Dweji-gomtang,</i> or pork soup.
- Yes.

15
00:00:47,881 --> 00:00:49,049
- In New York!
- That's right.

16
00:00:49,132 --> 00:00:51,009
THE WORLD'S HOTTEST

17
00:00:51,093 --> 00:00:55,847
<i>DWEJI-GOMTANG</i> RESTAURANT

18
00:00:56,431 --> 00:01:01,019
<i>Okdongsik's dweji-gomtang</i>
<i>was awarded the Michelin Bib Gourmand,</i>

19
